<DOC><DOCNO> AP880708-0137 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-08-88 1258EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u i PM-India-GasLeak 1stLd-Writethru a0615 07-08 0189</FIRST><SECOND>PM-India-Gas Leak, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0615,0190</SECOND><HEAD>Precede NEW DELHI</HEAD><HEAD>13 Die After Inhaling Carbon Dioxide</HEAD><NOTE>EDS: UPDATES thruout with official saying carbon dioxide blamedfor deaths.</NOTE><DATELINE>KARNAL, India (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Thirteen farmers died after they went intowells contaminated with carbon dioxide, a government official saidtoday.   Kartar Singh Bhoria, deputy commissioner in Karnal in thenorthern state of Haryana, said the deaths occurred Thursday andtoday in six villages near Karnal.   He said all of the farmers were stricken after they climbed intothe wells to start up underground pumps for irrigating ricepaddies. Tests showed the wells to be filled with carbon dioxide,he said.   The colorless and odorless gas was believed formed undergroundbecause of radical climate changes over the past year. Last yearthe region suffered severe drought.   Karnal is 72 miles north of New Delhi.   The Press Trust of India said other villages were warned ofpossible danger.   Government officials urged farmers to lower burning candles orlamps into the well to check for gas before entering the wellsthemselves. The flame will be extinguished if carbon dioxide gas ispresent, they said.</TEXT></DOC>